Spiritum corpo‑ reum voco aërem , vel potius ignem , qui pro ſui ſubtili‑ tate videri non po‑ te , & corpora in‑ terius vegetando viuificat; quædam autem vegetat tan‑ tùm & non ſen‑ ficat ,  cut arbores , herbas, & vniuerſa in terra germinan‑ tia;quædam ſen‑ ficat & vegetat ‑ cut omnia bruta animalia.
Vita brutorum a‑ nimalium e ſpi‑ ritus vitalis con‑ ans de aëre & ſanguine anima‑ lis, inuibilis , ſed ſenbilis ; memo‑ riam habens,intel‑ leu carens , cum carne moriens , in aëra euaneſcens.
